<a name="vt"></a><h2 class="h1" style="margin: 0px 0px 18px 0px; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;">Video transcript</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px <%=right_margin_split%>px 0px <%=left_margin_0%>px;">
Welcome to Bank of America. 
<br><br>
We&acute;re excited about your interest in joining our winning team and in becoming one of our valued Associates. We&acute;ve created this video to introduce you to the exciting positions in our Contact Centers and to outline some of the challenges and rewards of being an Associate in a contact center environment. 
<br><br>
In the next few minutes, we&acute;ll explain what we expect from our Associates and what you can expect from us. We hope that you&acute;ll be excited and interested in joining our team after you hear what we have to offer. 
<br><br>
If you decide that your skills and interests are not a match with contact center positions, just let us know. There may be other opportunities available within Bank of America that you would feel are a better match for your skills and interests. Our goal is to make sure you make the best decision for you, our company, and our customers. Either way, we hope that you will become or remain one of our valued customers. 
<br><br>
<b>Who We Are</b>
<br><br>
Bank of America employs more than 200,000 Associates from coast-to-coast and around the world. We provide full-service banking operations at nearly 6,000 banking centers across the country. We also serve our customers through easy access online banking and more than 17,000 ATMs. We continue to have the largest online banking customer base in the world. Bank of America is the number one overall Small Business Administration lender in the United States and number one SBA lender to minority-owned small businesses.
<br><br>
We provide International corporate financial services for business transactions in 175 countries.
<br><br>
Our company&acute;s stock is listed on the New York, Pacific and London stock exchanges, and certain shares are listed on the Tokyo stock exchange.
<br><br>
Bank of America is also very involved in the communities we serve. We generously support education, community development, the arts, and many other important initiatives.
<br><br>
Bank of America is consistently rated as one of the best places to work by a number of organizations, including "Working Mother" Magazine. At Bank of America, our commitment to the community and to our customers inspires everything we do and is evident in the standards of excellence to which we adhere.
<br><br>
These standards are what drive our commitment to deliver error-free service to customers in a warm and friendly manner. These standards also mean we strive to be easy to do business with and to create delightful customer experiences.
<br><br>
Simply put, at Bank of America, we want to create opportunity for our Associates, our customers and our shareholders in everything we do every day.
<br><br>
Within Bank of America, our Contact Center positions are part of the Customer Service and Support organization. As an Associate in the Contact Center, you will become an integral part of this organization and its vast resources. You will become part of a team that operates in an exciting contact center environment where you will interact with customers using a variety of methods such as phone, email and online. While interacting with customers as a Bank of America Associate, it is critical that you focus on providing service that delights our customers.
<br><br>
We want to ensure that our customers are not simply satisfied with the service they receive when they contact our Associates, but that they are delighted with their service and would recommend Bank of America to friends, family and co-workers.
<br><br>
To provide the highest level of service to our wide variety of customers, we strive to have the right number of Associates available to respond to our customers&acute; needs whenever they may need us. Being here for the customer, means that our Contact Center Associates work untraditional hours. Each of our Contact Centers has various hours of operations; some are open seven days a week, others work five or six days a week. Some sites are available to serve our customers 24 hours a day, while others end work at 10:00 p.m. or later. Because our customers rely on us every day, we&acute;re generally open most holidays. This ensures that we&acute;re here for our customers when they need us. It also means that we can offer our Associates a variety of schedules to fit their personal needs.
<br><br>
You&acute;ll also have the opportunity to grow professionally, to develop your skills, and explore new opportunities as you go.
<br><br>
Being an Associate in a Contact Center is a demanding, yet highly rewarding role. As you consider becoming an Associate in the Contact Center, you should be aware of the key characteristics of those who are typically successful in the role. Generally, they are people who are customer service-oriented. We are looking for people who enjoy and are effective at serving customers. They exhibit confidence, demonstrate a personal interest in resolving customer issues, possess strong communication skills; those who can communicate effectively with others and are good listeners. Problem solving is an important part of succeeding in this role, as are being caring, flexible, goal-oriented, a strong team player, professional, able to multi-task, and navigate easily through computer systems.
<br><br>
Associates are required to listen to customers and enter information into multiple systems simultaneously. To be effective, you must be able to effectively handle the multiple systems to create a seamless experience for our customers.
<br><br>
And how are you at demonstrating composure under stress? It&acute;s also important for Contact Center Associates to be comfortable establishing and nurturing relationships, since providing exceptional customer service is a must.
<br><br>
As a Contact Center Associate, you are Bank of America to our customers. These roles require not only a pleasant personality and a very strong customer focus, but also the ability to solve problems efficiently and identify opportunities to grow relationships with our customers.
<br><br>
Your success will depend on your ability to consistently meet goals and provide exceptional service to our customers in a first-call resolution environment.
<br><br>
At Bank of America, we expect a great deal from our Contact Center Associates. Those high expectations can present a number of challenges. Challenges that may make these valuable roles seem difficult at times. It is crucial that you consider all aspects of this position prior to deciding whether you want to work in a Contact Center for Bank of America.
<br><br>
<b>Challenges</b>
<br><br>
Those challenges may include strict adherence to work schedules. We develop schedules by estimating the call volumes that are anticipated at a given time. Each Associate is critical to the success of our business, and we cannot be successful without everyone&acute;s commitment to do his or her part. Therefore, it&acute;s vital for you to live up to the scheduling commitments, so that you can help make Bank of America one of the best places to work and with which to do business. 
<br><br>
At Bank of America, we&acute;re serious about serving our customers whenever they contact us, and we have specific policies and procedures in place to deal with absenteeism and punctuality. You can receive information from the recruiter regarding absenteeism and schedule adherence at Bank of America. If you determine that you will not be able to adhere to this type of schedule, you can opt out of consideration for this role.
<br><br>
Associates who work in our contact centers must also be willing to face the daily challenge of constant calls, coming in one call after the other. Working in a Contact Center means you&acute;re handling a significant number of calls per hour unless you&acute;re on break or at lunch. It&acute;s important for you to understand that you will need to be at your desk answering calls for the duration of your shift. 
<br><br>
Associates in our Contact Centers will also have to effectively manage difficult customers. The goal is to provide exceptional customer service, even in challenging situations, which will result in a positive experience for the customer. Some of the customers who call Bank of America may be dissatisfied with their service or even upset. It is important as a Contact Center Associate that you handle these calls in a professional way.
<br><br>
In order to provide our customers with the most accurate information, Associates in our Contact Centers are required to keep up to date on ever-changing information within the bank. 
<br><br>
Our Associates are encouraged to raise the level of their performance by meeting and exceeding service goals. This ensures that our Associates are professional as they strive to meet our customers&acute; needs.
<br><br>
<b>Rewards</b>
<br><br>
A position in one of our contact centers is more than just challenging. It&acute;s also extremely rewarding. Let&acute;s look at some of the rewards and opportunities in these positions.
<br><br>
They include enhanced customer service skills that can be transferred to other roles as you advance in your career within the bank. Your future is not limited here at Bank of America. By developing customer service skills in our Contact Centers, you&acute;ll be able to pave the way for future career success. 
<br><br>
Whether you&acute;re interested in pursuing the variety of careers available within our Contact Centers, or you&acute;d like to explore the broad range of careers throughout Bank of America, your experience as a Contact Center Associate can be a perfect choice for whatever career path you choose. Because our Contact Centers are located across the United States and offer positions for all experience levels, the opportunities for career advancement are endless.
<br><br>
Your role as a Contact Center Associate is crucial to the success of Bank of America.
<br><br>
Associates who work in our Contact Centers are given updated training so that they&acute;re aware of the latest developments and can provide customers with the latest information. Bank of America also offers impressive awards and incentives. We offer competitive salary and the potential to earn additional income through incentive programs that are designed to keep you motivated and to reward strong performance.
<br><br>
Bank of America also offers outstanding benefits that allow Associates to balance their profession and their personal lives.
<br><br>
Now you know more about Bank of America and career opportunities in our Contact Centers. After watching this video, you should be able to make an informed decision about applying for a position with us. We hope that you&acute;re excited about what you&acute;ve seen and that you&acute;ll want to join our team. 
<br><br>
Whatever your choice, we wish you good luck in the future, and we thank you for considering Bank of America in your job search.
</p>
